Today, the United States commemorates the Meds Yeghern, one of the worst mass atrocities of the 20th century, in which one and a half million Armenians were deported, massacred, or marched to their deaths during the final years of the Ottoman Empire. The US joins the Armenian community in mourning the lives lost and honors those who tried to end the violence. The contributions of Americans who helped save lives and rebuild Armenian communities are also recognized. The courage and resiliency of the Armenian people in building vibrant communities around the world, including in the US, are acknowledged. The US pledges to learn from past tragedies and supports the efforts of Armenians and Turks to acknowledge and reckon with their painful history. The commitment to a more peaceful world is reaffirmed.